fields.description:
Tested with Firefox 53

# Create a file
# Select TABS as indentation
# Use multiple indentation in the file
# View the file in Chrome and Firefox

Firefox only renders up to the first indentation. Subsequent indentation is not rendered.

Only affect is TABS is used for indentation. Space indentations works fine.

Removing this from CSS solves the issue

{code}
#!css

letter-spacing: -.005em;
{code}

On Firefox 53.0.2 (32bit) indents are broken when viewing code.

This is the case when the code you view uses tabs as indents.

If space is used the indents are correct.

You can have a look at an example.

https://bitbucket.org/frankmohaupt/public/src/111532a66d9d76ab8f0b06699fbcf5b99fb7a5ec/letter-spacing-issue.php?fileviewer=file-view-default

NOTE: Use Firefox to see the issue.

This issue is caused by a negative letter-spacing css setting:

{code}
#!css

letter-spacing: -0.005em;
{code}

While using [[SourceCode.txt|My Source Code]] syntax,\\
instead of showing -

{code}
#!python

https://bitbucket.org/<username>/<repo>/src/<commit Hash>/path/to/SourceCode.txt,
{code}

it added additional "<username>/<repo>" into the redirected link.\\
eg.

{code}
#!python

instead of showing https://bitbucket.org/<username>/<repo>/src/<commit Hash>/<username>/<repo>/path/to/SourceCode.txt
{code}
